Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <cloudyoncall> what do max utxo size and utxo sum mean in the sellers tab, and what do they mean in the buyers tab? because in buyers, for each price, the utxo size and sum are both 0

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <cloudyoncall> and i want to sell

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Hermes08> in this case when you make an order you won't see none in the order you set up , but liquidity providers already have a history and that's the average utxo size they have most of the time, if you are not seeing that type of information populating in other orders is because they are also normal users that' don't have so much trades or in this case they are not liquidty providers.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Hermes08> you should try to match the utxos size for trades depending on what pair you are swapping , you can do this by using the make inventory option next the coin you want to swap

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <cloudyoncall> so the buyers with 0 utxo size and sum, are not able to be filled? what then is the purpose of their bids?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Hermes08> they can be filled remember because of it being peer to peer and in many trades users don't have a long trading history it can take some time for that depth and that utxos columns to be updated

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Hermes08> if you want to test this before doing a trade you can use the beer and pizza faucet in order to get some initial trades going on
